	<string id="st_wpn_sks_short_descr">
		<text>The SKS is one of the first weapons chambered for the 7.62x39mm round. Replaced in Soviet front-line service by the AK-47 in the early 1950s, it remained in second-line service for decades and is still used as a ceremonial arm today. This rifle has had its barrel shortened, allowing it to act as a pistol, the gas tube has also been adjusted to maintain semi-automatic operation. The shortened barrel results in greatly decreased accuracy and muzzle velocity.\n
		%c[ui_gray_2]ATTACHMENTS: \n
		%c[d_purple]• %c[ui_gray_2] PU type scopes</text>
	</string>

